<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1437,152,755]" pageId="10" pageNumber="100">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,328,153,179]" pageId="10" pageNumber="100">Etymology</emphasis>
: This species is named in honor of Dr. Jürg De Marmels, acknowledging his generous help to solve several taxonomic problems regarding Colombian odonates. Prominent entomologist, curator of the Museo del Instituto de Zoología Agrícola Francisco Fernández Yépez of the Universidad Central de Venezuela, who has con- tributed greatly to the study of Neotropical Odonata including the genus 
<emphasis box="[965,1103,261,286]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="100">Heteragrion</emphasis>
here considered.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1437,152,755]" pageId="10" pageNumber="100">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,522,296,323]" pageId="10" pageNumber="100">Description of the holotype</emphasis>
: 
<emphasis box="[537,598,296,322]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="100">Head</emphasis>
: above yellow anteriorly, but mostly black between level of hind border of median ocellus and occipital margin, with small brown spots on vertex and between ocellus, rear of head yellow (
<figureCitation box="[160,248,368,395]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1465,1490]" captionTargetBox="[359,1216,453,1446]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[359,1227,453,1446]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 5. Face color pattern: H. calendulum (taken from Bota-Sierra &amp; Novelo-Gutierrez 2017): (A) male Pueblo Rico, Risaralda (B) female Pueblo Rico, Risaralda. Heteragrion demarmelsi: (C) male Leticia, Amazonas (D) female Leticia, Amazo- nas. Heteragrion erythrogastrum: (E) male Union Panamericana, Chocó (F) female Union Panamericana, Chocó. Heteragrion flavidorsum: (G) male PNN Churumbelos, Putumayo (H) female PNN Churumbelos, Putumayo. H. inca: (I) male Puerto Legui- zamo, Putumayo (J) female Puerto Leguizamo, Putumayo." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3415709" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3415709/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="100">Fig. 5C</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1437,152,755]" pageId="10" pageNumber="100">
<emphasis box="[199,313,404,430]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="100">Prothorax</emphasis>
: anterior lobe black on anterior margin and yellow on posterior margin, middle lobe yellow with two lateral and central black spots, posterior lobe black with two posterolateral yellow spots (
<figureCitation box="[1167,1273,440,467]" captionStart="FIGURE 16" captionStartId="17.[151,250,1180,1205]" captionTargetBox="[355,1230,190,1152]" captionTargetId="figure@17.[349,1237,181,1161]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="FIGURE 16. Female structures: H. tatama: PNN Tatamá, Risaralda (A) S9–10 lateral view (B) S9–10 ventral view (C) intersternite. Heteragrion demarmelsi: Leticia, Amazonas (D) male habitus (E) female habitus. Heteragrion angustipenne: Mocoa, Putumayo (F) female habitus. Heteragrion flavidorsum: PNN Churumbelos, Putumayo (G) female habitus. Heteragrion demarmelsi: Leticia, Amazonas (H) male thorax dorsal (I) female thorax dorsal. Heteragrion angustipenne: Mocoa, Putumayo (J) female throax dorsal. Heteragrion flavidorsum: PNN Churumbelos, Putumayo (K) female thorax dorsal." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3253608/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="100">Fig. 16H</figureCitation>
). 
<emphasis box="[1294,1428,440,466]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="100">Pterothorax</emphasis>
: yellow with black middorsal line, black oval band on mesepisternum which does not reach posterior border, green- ish antehumeral stripe, dark brown stripe on mesepimeron, and on metepisternum, the latter darker in the middle and becomes less defined toward its extremes (
<figureCitation box="[624,771,548,575]" captionStart="FIGURE 16" captionStartId="17.[151,250,1180,1205]" captionTargetBox="[355,1230,190,1152]" captionTargetId="figure@17.[349,1237,181,1161]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="FIGURE 16. Female structures: H. tatama: PNN Tatamá, Risaralda (A) S9–10 lateral view (B) S9–10 ventral view (C) intersternite. Heteragrion demarmelsi: Leticia, Amazonas (D) male habitus (E) female habitus. Heteragrion angustipenne: Mocoa, Putumayo (F) female habitus. Heteragrion flavidorsum: PNN Churumbelos, Putumayo (G) female habitus. Heteragrion demarmelsi: Leticia, Amazonas (H) male thorax dorsal (I) female thorax dorsal. Heteragrion angustipenne: Mocoa, Putumayo (J) female throax dorsal. Heteragrion flavidorsum: PNN Churumbelos, Putumayo (K) female thorax dorsal." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3253608/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="100">Figs. 16D, H</figureCitation>
). 
<emphasis box="[790,843,549,574]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="100">Legs</emphasis>
: pale brown with the distal 0.25 dark brown, spurs on femora about same size as space between them, except for distal four, which are two times as long as space between them; eight spurs on profemora and mesofemora and 11 on metafemora, spurs on tibiae two times as long as space between them, except for distal three, which are shorter, numbering eight on protibiae and mesotibiae and ten on metatibiae; tarsi and claws dark brown. 
<emphasis box="[598,666,693,718]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="100">Wings</emphasis>
: hyaline with brown tone, veins and pterostigma brown, the latter as long as 1.5–2 cells, with proximal and distal edges oblique, 20Px in FW and 18Px in HW.
</paragraph>
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3415717" ID-Zenodo-Dep="3415717" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3415717/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="100" startId="10.[151,250,1862,1887]" targetBox="[353,1234,776,1843]" targetPageId="10">
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1436,1862,1960]" pageId="10" pageNumber="100">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,274,1862,1887]" pageId="10" pageNumber="100">FIGURE 9.</emphasis>
Male cerci: 
<emphasis box="[400,548,1863,1887]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="100">H. demarmelsi</emphasis>
: Leticia, Amazonas (A) dorsal view (B) mediodorsal view (C) lateral view. 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="100">Heteragrion erythrogastrum</emphasis>
: Union Panamericana, Chocó (D) dorsal view (E) mediodorsal view (F) lateral view. 
<emphasis box="[1177,1429,1899,1923]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="100">Heteragrion flavidorsum</emphasis>
: PNN Churumbelos, Putumayo (G) dorsal view (H) mediodorsal view (I) lateral view. 
<emphasis box="[1022,1067,1935,1959]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="100">VbC</emphasis>
: Ventro basal convexity.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1437,153,539]" pageId="11" pageNumber="101">
<emphasis box="[199,305,153,179]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="101">Abdomen</emphasis>
: mainly black, S1–S2 yellow laterally, S1–S3 black with a thin yellow dorsal line, S3–S7 black with a yellow basal ring, S3–S6 black with a yellow lateroventral spot on distal half, S7 dark brown on distal two thirds, S8 dark brown with yellow dorsal spot, S9–S10 dark brown (
<figureCitation box="[828,932,225,252]" captionStart="FIGURE 16" captionStartId="17.[151,250,1180,1205]" captionTargetBox="[355,1230,190,1152]" captionTargetId="figure@17.[349,1237,181,1161]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="FIGURE 16. Female structures: H. tatama: PNN Tatamá, Risaralda (A) S9–10 lateral view (B) S9–10 ventral view (C) intersternite. Heteragrion demarmelsi: Leticia, Amazonas (D) male habitus (E) female habitus. Heteragrion angustipenne: Mocoa, Putumayo (F) female habitus. Heteragrion flavidorsum: PNN Churumbelos, Putumayo (G) female habitus. Heteragrion demarmelsi: Leticia, Amazonas (H) male thorax dorsal (I) female thorax dorsal. Heteragrion angustipenne: Mocoa, Putumayo (J) female throax dorsal. Heteragrion flavidorsum: PNN Churumbelos, Putumayo (K) female thorax dorsal." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3253608/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="101">Fig. 16D</figureCitation>
); genital ligula has the typical morphology of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Selys" authorityYear="1862" box="[151,289,262,287]" class="Insecta" family="Megapodagrionidae" genus="Heteragrion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="11" pageNumber="101" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,289,262,287]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="101">Heteragrion</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species (
<bibRefCitation author="Williamson, E. B." box="[390,587,261,287]" pageId="11" pageNumber="101" pagination="1 - 88" refId="ref12284" refString="Williamson, E. B. (1919) Results of the University of Michigan - Williamson expedition to Colombia, 1916 - 17. IV. Notes on species of the genus Heteragrion Selys with descriptions of new species (Odonata). Occasional Papers of the Museum of Zoology, University of Michigan, 68, 1 - 88. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. part. 14454" type="journal article" year="1919">Williamson 1919</bibRefCitation>
). 
<emphasis box="[605,666,261,287]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="101">Cerci</emphasis>
: dark brown with black spots, distance between bifurcation of medial process and tip of cerci close to one third the length of cerci (
<figureCitation box="[836,926,297,323]" captionStart="FIGURE 9" captionStartId="10.[151,250,1862,1887]" captionTargetBox="[353,1234,776,1843]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[353,1234,776,1843]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 9. Male cerci: H. demarmelsi: Leticia, Amazonas (A) dorsal view (B) mediodorsal view (C) lateral view. Heteragrion erythrogastrum: Union Panamericana, Chocó (D) dorsal view (E) mediodorsal view (F) lateral view. Heteragrion flavidorsum: PNN Churumbelos, Putumayo (G) dorsal view (H) mediodorsal view (I) lateral view. VbC: Ventro basal convexity." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3415717" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3415717/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="101">Fig. 9A</figureCitation>
), slight ventrobasal convexity in mediodorsal view (
<figureCitation box="[222,309,333,359]" captionStart="FIGURE 9" captionStartId="10.[151,250,1862,1887]" captionTargetBox="[353,1234,776,1843]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[353,1234,776,1843]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 9. Male cerci: H. demarmelsi: Leticia, Amazonas (A) dorsal view (B) mediodorsal view (C) lateral view. Heteragrion erythrogastrum: Union Panamericana, Chocó (D) dorsal view (E) mediodorsal view (F) lateral view. Heteragrion flavidorsum: PNN Churumbelos, Putumayo (G) dorsal view (H) mediodorsal view (I) lateral view. VbC: Ventro basal convexity." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3415717" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3415717/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="101">Fig. 9B</figureCitation>
), curved in lateral view (
<figureCitation box="[592,681,333,359]" captionStart="FIGURE 9" captionStartId="10.[151,250,1862,1887]" captionTargetBox="[353,1234,776,1843]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[353,1234,776,1843]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 9. Male cerci: H. demarmelsi: Leticia, Amazonas (A) dorsal view (B) mediodorsal view (C) lateral view. Heteragrion erythrogastrum: Union Panamericana, Chocó (D) dorsal view (E) mediodorsal view (F) lateral view. Heteragrion flavidorsum: PNN Churumbelos, Putumayo (G) dorsal view (H) mediodorsal view (I) lateral view. VbC: Ventro basal convexity." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3415717" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3415717/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="101">Fig. 9C</figureCitation>
). 
<emphasis box="[702,827,334,359]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="101">Paraprocts</emphasis>
: yellow with black tip, spinelike, about 1/4 the length of cerci (
<figureCitation box="[251,333,369,395]" captionStart="FIGURE 9" captionStartId="10.[151,250,1862,1887]" captionTargetBox="[353,1234,776,1843]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[353,1234,776,1843]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 9. Male cerci: H. demarmelsi: Leticia, Amazonas (A) dorsal view (B) mediodorsal view (C) lateral view. Heteragrion erythrogastrum: Union Panamericana, Chocó (D) dorsal view (E) mediodorsal view (F) lateral view. Heteragrion flavidorsum: PNN Churumbelos, Putumayo (G) dorsal view (H) mediodorsal view (I) lateral view. VbC: Ventro basal convexity." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3415717" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3415717/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="101">Fig 9C</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="12" lastPageNumber="102" pageId="11" pageNumber="101" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1437,153,539]" box="[199,861,405,431]" pageId="11" pageNumber="101">
<emphasis box="[199,361,406,431]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="101">Measurements</emphasis>
(mm): Abdomen: 38.0, FW: 23.0, HW:24.0.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1437,153,539]" pageId="11" pageNumber="101">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,511,440,467]" pageId="11" pageNumber="101">
Description of the 
<typeStatus box="[416,511,441,467]" pageId="11" pageNumber="101">allotype</typeStatus>
</emphasis>
: 
<emphasis box="[525,586,441,467]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="101">Head</emphasis>
: mainly dark brown with black clypeus, postfrons grayish followed by black spots on each side of antennae, light brown portion between antennae and vertex, and posterior margin of head black, rear of head dark brown (
<figureCitation box="[510,600,512,539]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1465,1490]" captionTargetBox="[359,1216,453,1446]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[359,1227,453,1446]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 5. Face color pattern: H. calendulum (taken from Bota-Sierra &amp; Novelo-Gutierrez 2017): (A) male Pueblo Rico, Risaralda (B) female Pueblo Rico, Risaralda. Heteragrion demarmelsi: (C) male Leticia, Amazonas (D) female Leticia, Amazo- nas. Heteragrion erythrogastrum: (E) male Union Panamericana, Chocó (F) female Union Panamericana, Chocó. Heteragrion flavidorsum: (G) male PNN Churumbelos, Putumayo (H) female PNN Churumbelos, Putumayo. H. inca: (I) male Puerto Legui- zamo, Putumayo (J) female Puerto Leguizamo, Putumayo." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3415709" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3415709/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="101">Fig. 5D</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<caption httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3253598/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="101" startId="11.[151,250,1699,1724]" targetBox="[353,1227,569,1672]" targetPageId="11">
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1437,1699,1796]" pageId="11" pageNumber="101">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,290,1699,1724]" pageId="11" pageNumber="101">FIGURE 10.</emphasis>
Male cerci: 
<taxonomicName authority=": Orito" authorityName="Orito" box="[424,572,1699,1724]" class="Insecta" family="Megapodagrionidae" genus="Heteragrion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="11" pageNumber="101" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="inca">
<emphasis box="[424,501,1700,1723]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="101">H. inca</emphasis>
: Orito
</taxonomicName>
, Putumayo (A) dorsal view (B) mediodorsal view (C) lateral view. 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="101">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Selys" authorityYear="1862" box="[1278,1403,1700,1723]" class="Insecta" family="Megapodagrionidae" genus="Heteragrion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="11" pageNumber="101" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Heteragrion</taxonomicName>
m. atroterminatum
</emphasis>
: Union Panamericana, Chocó (D) dorsal view (E) mediodorsal view (F) lateral view. 
<emphasis box="[1174,1429,1736,1759]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="101">
<emphasis box="[1174,1331,1736,1759]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="101">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Selys" authorityYear="1862" box="[1174,1299,1736,1759]" class="Insecta" family="Megapodagrionidae" genus="Heteragrion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="11" pageNumber="101" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Heteragrion</taxonomicName>
m.
</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority=": Puerto Berrio" authorityName="Puerto Berrio" class="Insecta" family="Megapodagrionidae" genus="Heteragrion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="11" pageNumber="101" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mitratum">
<emphasis box="[1336,1429,1736,1759]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="101">mitratum</emphasis>
: Puerto Berrio
</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
, Antioquia (G) dorsal view (H) mediodorsal view (I) lateral view. 
<emphasis box="[963,1008,1771,1795]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="101">VbC</emphasis>
: Ventro basal convexity.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1436,1842,2012]" lastBlockId="12.[151,1437,153,899]" lastPageId="12" lastPageNumber="102" pageId="11" pageNumber="101">
<emphasis box="[199,313,1842,1868]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="101">Prothorax</emphasis>
: anterior and middle lobe brownish, posterior lobe brown with paler spots on each side (
<figureCitation box="[1329,1422,1842,1869]" captionStart="FIGURE 16" captionStartId="17.[151,250,1180,1205]" captionTargetBox="[355,1230,190,1152]" captionTargetId="figure@17.[349,1237,181,1161]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="FIGURE 16. Female structures: H. tatama: PNN Tatamá, Risaralda (A) S9–10 lateral view (B) S9–10 ventral view (C) intersternite. Heteragrion demarmelsi: Leticia, Amazonas (D) male habitus (E) female habitus. Heteragrion angustipenne: Mocoa, Putumayo (F) female habitus. Heteragrion flavidorsum: PNN Churumbelos, Putumayo (G) female habitus. Heteragrion demarmelsi: Leticia, Amazonas (H) male thorax dorsal (I) female thorax dorsal. Heteragrion angustipenne: Mocoa, Putumayo (J) female throax dorsal. Heteragrion flavidorsum: PNN Churumbelos, Putumayo (K) female thorax dorsal." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3253608/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="101">
Fig. 
<date box="[1383,1422,1842,1869]" pageId="11" pageNumber="101" value="2016-01">16I</date>
</figureCitation>
), dorsal plate of intersternite with anterior portion more acute than posterior portion (
<figureCitation box="[1103,1197,1878,1904]" captionStart="FIGURE 14" captionStartId="15.[151,250,1334,1359]" captionTargetBox="[378,1207,314,1306]" captionTargetId="figure@15.[370,1218,309,1314]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="FIGURE 14. Female structures: H. erythrogastrum: Union Panamericana, Chocó (A) S9–10 lateral view (B) S9–10 ventral view (C) intersternite. Heteragrion flavidorsum: PNN Churumbelos, Putumayo (D) S9–10 lateral view (E) S9–10 ventral view (F) intersternite. H. demarmelsi: Leticia, Amazonas (G) S9–10 lateral view (H) S9–10 ventral view (I) intersternite." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3253604/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="101">
Fig. 
<date box="[1157,1197,1878,1904]" pageId="11" pageNumber="101" value="2014-01">14I</date>
</figureCitation>
). 
<emphasis box="[1219,1353,1878,1904]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="101">Pterothorax</emphasis>
: mesepisternum pale brown with black middorsal line and brown antehumeral stripe, mesepimeron pale brown with brown stripe, mesinfraepisternum pale brown with brown spot, metepisternum pale brown with dark brown stripe, metepimeron pale yellow with short brown stripe, metainfraepisternum pale yellow with brown spot (
<figureCitation box="[1288,1422,1986,2012]" captionStart="FIGURE 16" captionStartId="17.[151,250,1180,1205]" captionTargetBox="[355,1230,190,1152]" captionTargetId="figure@17.[349,1237,181,1161]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="FIGURE 16. Female structures: H. tatama: PNN Tatamá, Risaralda (A) S9–10 lateral view (B) S9–10 ventral view (C) intersternite. Heteragrion demarmelsi: Leticia, Amazonas (D) male habitus (E) female habitus. Heteragrion angustipenne: Mocoa, Putumayo (F) female habitus. Heteragrion flavidorsum: PNN Churumbelos, Putumayo (G) female habitus. Heteragrion demarmelsi: Leticia, Amazonas (H) male thorax dorsal (I) female thorax dorsal. Heteragrion angustipenne: Mocoa, Putumayo (J) female throax dorsal. Heteragrion flavidorsum: PNN Churumbelos, Putumayo (K) female thorax dorsal." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3253608/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="101">Figs. 16E, I</figureCitation>
). 
<emphasis box="[151,204,154,179]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="102">Legs</emphasis>
: dark brown, spurs on femora about same size as space between them, except for distal three, which are two times as long as space between them on profemora and mesofemora, numbering six on profemora and mesofemora and ten on metafemora; spurs on tibiae about two times as long as space between them, except for distal three, which are shorter, eight on protibiae and mesotibiae and ten on metatibiae, tarsi and claws dark brown. 
<emphasis box="[1216,1284,262,287]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="102">Wings</emphasis>
: hyaline with a slight brown tone, brown veins and pale brown pterostigma which covers 2.5 cells and has proximal edge oblique and distal edge vertical, 20Px in FW and 17Px in HW.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="12.[151,1437,153,899]" pageId="12" pageNumber="102">
<emphasis box="[199,305,369,395]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="102">Abdomen</emphasis>
: mainly dark brown, S1 pale brown with a slight brown dorsal spot, S2–S5 with a narrow pale brown dorsal line, S2 pale brown laterally, S3–7 with pale brown basal ring, S3–S6 with a pale brown lateroventral spot on posterior half, S9–S10 brown dorsally and pale brown ventrally (
<figureCitation box="[920,1023,441,468]" captionStart="FIGURE 16" captionStartId="17.[151,250,1180,1205]" captionTargetBox="[355,1230,190,1152]" captionTargetId="figure@17.[349,1237,181,1161]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="FIGURE 16. Female structures: H. tatama: PNN Tatamá, Risaralda (A) S9–10 lateral view (B) S9–10 ventral view (C) intersternite. Heteragrion demarmelsi: Leticia, Amazonas (D) male habitus (E) female habitus. Heteragrion angustipenne: Mocoa, Putumayo (F) female habitus. Heteragrion flavidorsum: PNN Churumbelos, Putumayo (G) female habitus. Heteragrion demarmelsi: Leticia, Amazonas (H) male thorax dorsal (I) female thorax dorsal. Heteragrion angustipenne: Mocoa, Putumayo (J) female throax dorsal. Heteragrion flavidorsum: PNN Churumbelos, Putumayo (K) female thorax dorsal." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3253608/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="102">Fig. 16E</figureCitation>
). 
<emphasis box="[1042,1162,441,467]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="102">Ovipositor</emphasis>
: pale brown, surpassing distal border of S10, but not tip of cerci, stylus pale brown (
<figureCitation box="[830,935,477,503]" captionStart="FIGURE 14" captionStartId="15.[151,250,1334,1359]" captionTargetBox="[378,1207,314,1306]" captionTargetId="figure@15.[370,1218,309,1314]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="FIGURE 14. Female structures: H. erythrogastrum: Union Panamericana, Chocó (A) S9–10 lateral view (B) S9–10 ventral view (C) intersternite. Heteragrion flavidorsum: PNN Churumbelos, Putumayo (D) S9–10 lateral view (E) S9–10 ventral view (F) intersternite. H. demarmelsi: Leticia, Amazonas (G) S9–10 lateral view (H) S9–10 ventral view (I) intersternite." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3253604/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="102">Fig. 14G</figureCitation>
), one ventral row of small teeth in a parallel arrangement on genital valves (
<figureCitation box="[503,607,513,539]" captionStart="FIGURE 14" captionStartId="15.[151,250,1334,1359]" captionTargetBox="[378,1207,314,1306]" captionTargetId="figure@15.[370,1218,309,1314]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="FIGURE 14. Female structures: H. erythrogastrum: Union Panamericana, Chocó (A) S9–10 lateral view (B) S9–10 ventral view (C) intersternite. Heteragrion flavidorsum: PNN Churumbelos, Putumayo (D) S9–10 lateral view (E) S9–10 ventral view (F) intersternite. H. demarmelsi: Leticia, Amazonas (G) S9–10 lateral view (H) S9–10 ventral view (I) intersternite." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3253604/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="102">Fig. 14H</figureCitation>
), cerci yellow basally and black distally (
<figureCitation box="[1071,1175,513,539]" captionStart="FIGURE 14" captionStartId="15.[151,250,1334,1359]" captionTargetBox="[378,1207,314,1306]" captionTargetId="figure@15.[370,1218,309,1314]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="FIGURE 14. Female structures: H. erythrogastrum: Union Panamericana, Chocó (A) S9–10 lateral view (B) S9–10 ventral view (C) intersternite. Heteragrion flavidorsum: PNN Churumbelos, Putumayo (D) S9–10 lateral view (E) S9–10 ventral view (F) intersternite. H. demarmelsi: Leticia, Amazonas (G) S9–10 lateral view (H) S9–10 ventral view (I) intersternite." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3253604/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="102">Fig. 14G</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="12.[151,1437,153,899]" box="[199,861,548,575]" pageId="12" pageNumber="102">
<emphasis box="[199,361,550,575]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="102">Measurements</emphasis>
(mm): Abdomen: 29.0, FW: 23.5, HW:24.0.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="12.[151,1437,153,899]" pageId="12" pageNumber="102">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,524,584,611]" pageId="12" pageNumber="102">
Variation among 
<typeStatus box="[406,524,585,611]" pageId="12" pageNumber="102">paratypes</typeStatus>
</emphasis>
: males: some 
<typeStatus box="[684,791,585,611]" pageId="12" pageNumber="102">paratypes</typeStatus>
have a faint brown to black stripe on metepimeron, abdomen 36.0–38.0mm, FW 23.0–24.0mm, Px in FW 19–21, HW 23.0–24.0, Px in HW 17–20. Females: similar, abdomen 
<quantity box="[206,323,657,683]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.85" metricValueMax="2.9" metricValueMin="2.8" pageId="12" pageNumber="102" unit="mm" value="28.5" valueMax="29.0" valueMin="28.0">28–29mm</quantity>
, FW 23.5–24.0mm, Px in FW 20.0mm, HW 24.0mm, Px in HW 17–18.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="12" pageNumber="102" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="12.[151,1437,153,899]" pageId="12" pageNumber="102">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,314,692,719]" pageId="12" pageNumber="102">Diagnosis</emphasis>
: when compared with the key provided for males by 
<bibRefCitation author="Williamson, E. B." box="[907,1119,693,719]" pageId="12" pageNumber="102" pagination="1 - 88" refId="ref12284" refString="Williamson, E. B. (1919) Results of the University of Michigan - Williamson expedition to Colombia, 1916 - 17. IV. Notes on species of the genus Heteragrion Selys with descriptions of new species (Odonata). Occasional Papers of the Museum of Zoology, University of Michigan, 68, 1 - 88. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. part. 14454" type="journal article" year="1919">Williamson (1919)</bibRefCitation>
, the male of the new species matches 
<taxonomicName box="[250,333,730,755]" class="Insecta" family="Megapodagrionidae" genus="Heteragrion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="12" pageNumber="102" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="inca">
<emphasis box="[250,333,730,755]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="102">H. inca</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, from which it differs by its strongly curved cerci, in lateral view (
<figureCitation box="[1086,1174,729,755]" captionStart="FIGURE 9" captionStartId="10.[151,250,1862,1887]" captionTargetBox="[353,1234,776,1843]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[353,1234,776,1843]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 9. Male cerci: H. demarmelsi: Leticia, Amazonas (A) dorsal view (B) mediodorsal view (C) lateral view. Heteragrion erythrogastrum: Union Panamericana, Chocó (D) dorsal view (E) mediodorsal view (F) lateral view. Heteragrion flavidorsum: PNN Churumbelos, Putumayo (G) dorsal view (H) mediodorsal view (I) lateral view. VbC: Ventro basal convexity." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3415717" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3415717/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="102">Fig. 9C</figureCitation>
). This cercus curvature in lateral view is similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="De Marmels, 1989" authorityName="De Marmels" authorityYear="1989" box="[465,908,765,791]" class="Insecta" family="Megapodagrionidae" genus="Heteragrion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="12" pageNumber="102" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="chlorotaeniatum">
<emphasis box="[465,685,765,791]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="102">H. chlorotaeniatum</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="De Marmels, J." box="[693,908,765,791]" pageId="12" pageNumber="102" pagination="1 - 78" refId="ref11677" refString="De Marmels, J. (1989) Odonata or dragonflies from Cerro de la Neblina. Academia de las Ciencias Fisicas, Matematicas y Naturales, Caracas, Venezuela, 25, 1 - 78." type="journal article" year="1989">De Marmels, 1989</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, but the latter has, in cercus middorsal view, a pointy ventrobasal convexity (angle similar to 90°). 
<taxonomicName authority="Daigle, 2005" authorityName="Daigle" authorityYear="2005" box="[736,1139,800,827]" class="Insecta" family="Megapodagrionidae" genus="Heteragrion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="12" pageNumber="102" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bickorum">
